In [4]:
# drop columns that I do not need for analysis; I don't need a name, number of siblings or kids, etc. 
# I decided not to include cabin because people may not have been in their cabin at the time of the crash. 
# I also did not care about where a passenger embarked from or how much they paid in fare, etc. 
# I only cared about if they survived, the class, sex, and age of the passenger since in an emergency, 
# this would have been the best way to categorize who would be rescued first. 

drop_train_df = train_df.drop(columns=['Name', 'SibSp', 'Parch', 'Ticket', 'Cabin', 'Embarked'])
drop_train_df.head()

# Interestingly, we see that more females than males survived across all three classes

# death incidence.
